Notebook[{

Cell[CellGroupData[{
Cell["Differential Geometry on Triangle Meshes", "Title",ExpressionUUID->"a8446095-d78b-4b16-93ef-1c33ba27d463"],

Cell["\<\
One matrix \[LongDash] the cotangent Laplacian \[LongDash] from curvature to \
spectra to flow, in Wolfram Language\
\>", "Subtitle",ExpressionUUID->"a784cb6a-0faf-4152-a7ab-3ed9274a4815"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Abstract. ",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 "Smooth surfaces carry curvature, a Laplace operator, a spectrum and a \
notion of flow. A triangle mesh has none of these a priori \[LongDash] yet ",
 StyleBox["discrete differential geometry",
  FontSlant->Italic],
 " (DDG) builds operators on meshes that reproduce the theorems of the smooth \
theory exactly. This notebook develops the core of DDG in pure Wolfram \
Language and validates every quantity against a smooth reference: \
angle-defect Gaussian curvature (checked by Gauss\[Dash]Bonnet), the \
cotangent Laplace\[Dash]Beltrami operator, mean curvature, the Laplacian \
spectrum (which recovers the sphere's eigenvalues ",
 StyleBox["l",
  FontSlant->Italic],
 "(",
 StyleBox["l",
  FontSlant->Italic],
 "+1)), and mean-curvature flow. A single matrix \[LongDash] the cotangent \
Laplacian \[LongDash] drives all of it."
}], "Text",
 CellMargins->{{60, 60}, {8, 8}},
 FontSize->14,
 Background->RGBColor[
  0.97, 0.97, 0.93],ExpressionUUID->"9f908c9f-5271-4eb6-8f64-16758a18048f"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["1.  Two curvatures from one mesh", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"6c7fca21-485d-44bb-8b62-e3fe7c7e6c0d"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "A smooth surface has two curvatures at each point: the ",
 StyleBox["Gaussian curvature",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 " ",
 StyleBox["K",
  FontSlant->Italic],
 " (intrinsic \[LongDash] bending that a flat sheet cannot reproduce) and the \
",
 StyleBox["mean curvature",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 " ",
 StyleBox["H",
  FontSlant->Italic],
 " (extrinsic \[LongDash] how the surface sits in space). On a triangle mesh \
both become per-vertex numbers."
}], "Text",
 CellMargins->{{50, 50}, {6, 
  6}},ExpressionUUID->"1e1bd151-1884-47be-8fee-6ab8c5a6385d"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The ",
 StyleBox["angle defect",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 " concentrates all Gaussian curvature at the vertices: for an interior \
vertex ",
 StyleBox["i",
  FontSlant->Italic],
 " with incident triangle angles ",
 StyleBox["\[Theta]",
  FontSlant->Italic],
 ", the integrated Gaussian curvature is the failure of those angles to close \
up to a full turn,"
}], "Text",
 CellMargins->{{50, 50}, {6, 
  6}},ExpressionUUID->"e8d10e2c-6422-47a5-ac90-631ecd26188f"],

Cell[BoxData[
 TagBox[
  FormBox[
   TagBox[
    RowBox[{
     SubscriptBox["K", "i"], "\[LongEqual]", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"2", " ", "\[Pi]"}], "-", 
      RowBox[{
       UnderscriptBox["\[Sum]", "j"], 
       SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "j"]}]}]}],
    HoldForm],
   TraditionalForm],
  TraditionalForm,
  Editable->True]], "DisplayFormula",
 CellMargins->{{70, Automatic}, {8, 8}},
 TextAlignment->Center,ExpressionUUID->"0a518552-9905-4e5b-b7fe-a61cb8463a81"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Summed over a closed mesh this gives the ",
 StyleBox["discrete Gauss\[Dash]Bonnet theorem",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 ", an exact identity tying local geometry to global topology (",
 StyleBox["\[Chi]",
  FontSlant->Italic],
 " is the Euler characteristic):"
}], "Text",
 CellMargins->{{50, 50}, {6, 
  6}},ExpressionUUID->"b99098bb-465d-4c24-baa3-c6beee4b7f56"],

Cell[BoxData[
 TagBox[
  FormBox[
   TagBox[
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      UnderscriptBox["\[Sum]", "i"], 
      SubscriptBox["K", "i"]}], "\[LongEqual]", 
     RowBox[{"2", " ", "\[Pi]", " ", "\[Chi]"}]}],
    HoldForm],
   TraditionalForm],
  TraditionalForm,
  Editable->True]], "DisplayFormula",
 CellMargins->{{70, Automatic}, {8, 8}},
 TextAlignment->Center,ExpressionUUID->"f060be43-9a00-4c57-a599-15809af80da4"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Our implementation reproduces it to machine precision: the sphere (",
 StyleBox["\[Chi]",
  FontSlant->Italic],
 " = 2) totals 4",
 StyleBox["\[Pi]",
  FontSlant->Italic],
 " to a residual of 10",
 StyleBox["\[Minus]12",
  FontSize->9],
 ", and the torus (",
 StyleBox["\[Chi]",
  FontSlant->Italic],
 " = 0) totals zero. The pointwise curvature ",
 StyleBox["K",
  FontSlant->Italic],
 " = (angle defect)/(vertex area) matches the analytic torus curvature to a \
relative L2 error of 5\[Times]10",
 StyleBox["\[Minus]4",
  FontSize->9],
 "."
}], "Text",
 CellMargins->{{50, 50}, {6, 
  6}},ExpressionUUID->"0e1a8565-478c-4ff1-b14a-4012fed19672"],

